If a simple string generation without any XML validation is ok for you, you should go with the solution of @a_horse_with_no_name.

If you want to create the XML elements using the XML functions of PostgreSQL, you need to generate a dynamic SQL with a formatted function:

[demo:db&lt;&gt;fiddle][1]

    CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION create_xml(_name text, _val boolean) RETURNS xml
    AS $$
    DECLARE
        _result xml;
    BEGIN
        EXECUTE format(&#39;SELECT xmlelement(name %I, %s)&#39;, _name, _val::text) INTO _result;
        
        RETURN _result;
    END;
    $$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

The problem is, that the element name cannot be set dynamically per record: [See here][2]


